WEBVTT

00:04.670 --> 00:07.380
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.460 --> 00:10.300
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:10.380 --> 00:12.090
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.170 --> 00:15.180
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.260 --> 00:17.550
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.640 --> 00:20.770
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.850 --> 00:22.890
♪ I want to stay with you ♪

00:22.980 --> 00:27.400
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:27.480 --> 00:32.900
♪♪

00:32.990 --> 00:36.450
Your faithful soldiers
are once again ready for battle.

00:36.530 --> 00:39.580
No braver soldiers
have ever there been.

00:39.660 --> 00:41.330
[ Gasps ]

00:41.410 --> 00:42.910
[ Laughs ]

00:43.000 --> 00:45.120
Brave soldier, are you sure
you're prepared

00:45.210 --> 00:48.750
to dive headfirst into magma,
just to protect your queen?

00:48.840 --> 00:50.210
"Yes, Your Majesty.

00:50.300 --> 00:53.300
Wait, on second thought, no!"

00:53.380 --> 00:55.590
The queen thanks you
for your service.

00:55.680 --> 00:57.470
Ahhh!

00:57.550 --> 00:59.010
[ Knock on door ]

00:59.100 --> 01:01.680
The universe truly
is cold and indifferent.

01:01.770 --> 01:03.100
I'll be right back.

01:03.180 --> 01:05.390
You'd better maintain
your integrity, soldier.

01:06.190 --> 01:07.940
[ Hisses ]

01:08.020 --> 01:09.610
Hi, Susie.
Good morning.

01:09.690 --> 01:11.860
As you know,
I'm a super-strong person.

01:11.940 --> 01:13.610
I'm captain
of my softball team.

01:13.690 --> 01:15.110
I drink my tea hot.

01:15.200 --> 01:17.450
And I leave the crusts
on my ham and cheeses.

01:17.530 --> 01:20.830
Not because my mom said,
but because it hardens me.

01:20.910 --> 01:22.330
We get it.
You're a jock.

01:22.410 --> 01:23.450
Big whoop.

01:23.540 --> 01:25.460
I guess what I'm trying
to say is,

01:25.540 --> 01:28.830
I am ready to learn
my magical identity today.

01:31.250 --> 01:32.210
Alright, kid.

01:32.300 --> 01:33.460
You think you're ready?

01:33.550 --> 01:34.760
I'm ready, baby!

01:34.840 --> 01:36.880
You think you're ready
to know what I know?

01:36.970 --> 01:38.380
Yeah!

01:38.470 --> 01:41.640
Well, if you think you're
ready, just go to the fjords.

01:41.720 --> 01:45.270
You'll find everything you need
right there in the fjords.

01:45.350 --> 01:46.560
The fjords!

01:46.640 --> 01:47.730
Ryan!

01:47.810 --> 01:50.560
Take Alexa to the fjords,
please!

01:52.520 --> 01:53.820
I've never been
to the fjords.

01:53.900 --> 01:57.150
Oh, my gosh, you're gonna
love the fjords.

01:57.240 --> 02:01.410
It's super-cold out there,
though, so take these, uh,

02:01.490 --> 02:02.740
pocket warmers.

02:02.830 --> 02:04.290
They're ineffectual
at best.

02:04.370 --> 02:05.660
An impulse purchase.

02:05.750 --> 02:07.210
Alright, off to the fjords
with you

02:07.290 --> 02:10.920
before I change my mind.
-Okay, I'm ready.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.340
Oh, are you now?

02:12.420 --> 02:13.460
[ Grunts ]

02:15.590 --> 02:18.510
Keep it together.
Keep it together.

02:18.590 --> 02:21.050
Ohh! [ Groans ]

02:21.140 --> 02:22.510
Don't fret, Suz.

02:22.600 --> 02:24.010
There's always tomorrow.

02:24.100 --> 02:28.350
♪♪

02:28.430 --> 02:30.230
Just drop me wherever.

02:30.310 --> 02:32.360
[ Laughs ]
Can you imagine?

02:32.440 --> 02:33.690
Okay, bye!

02:33.770 --> 02:35.860
Aaaaahhhh! Ugh!

02:35.940 --> 02:39.950
Uh! Totally forgot crows
are completely tone-deaf.

02:40.030 --> 02:41.530
Thanks a lot, Ryan.

02:43.410 --> 02:44.700
Hey.
Hello, ma'am.

02:44.780 --> 02:46.790
May I get a lay
of the land, please?

02:46.870 --> 02:48.830
Fer sher.

02:48.910 --> 02:50.540
Ah, the fjords.

02:50.620 --> 02:51.710
Ryan was right.

02:51.790 --> 02:53.290
I love them.

02:53.380 --> 02:54.840
Introduce yourself.

02:54.920 --> 02:56.090
Hi, fjords.

02:56.170 --> 02:57.800
[ Echoing ] I'm Skadi.

02:57.880 --> 03:01.090
[ Gasps ] Hi, fjords!
I'm Alexa!

03:01.180 --> 03:04.970
Hi, Alexa.
So you must be our new giant.

03:05.050 --> 03:06.350
[ Gasps ] Giant?

03:06.430 --> 03:08.180
Oh, my gosh, yes!
I knew it!

03:08.270 --> 03:11.560
I'm tall, I'm sporty,
I'm captain of my softball team.

03:11.640 --> 03:13.900
And I bet you've got
a couple fists

03:13.980 --> 03:15.320
if you put in the effort.

03:15.400 --> 03:16.400
[ Straining ]

03:16.480 --> 03:17.440
[ Farts ]

03:17.530 --> 03:19.320
Beautiful knuckles.

03:19.400 --> 03:20.990
We're gonna need those.

03:21.070 --> 03:23.570
Use 'em to punch a little cloud,
control a little weather,

03:23.660 --> 03:26.030
benefit nature
in a generalized way.

03:26.120 --> 03:27.240
Put me in, Coach!

03:27.330 --> 03:29.540
I'm ready to be captain
of the giants!

03:29.620 --> 03:30.870
Ha ha. Captain?

03:30.960 --> 03:32.580
You're hardly a rookie,
slugger.

03:32.670 --> 03:34.330
So let's put a pin
in the captain thing

03:34.420 --> 03:37.130
and focus on training up
those fists, huh?

03:37.210 --> 03:39.090
C'mon, fist bump.

03:39.170 --> 03:40.800
Oh, yeah, there it is.

03:40.880 --> 03:42.720
Can you, uh,
put me down now?

03:42.800 --> 03:44.260
My neck is kinda hurting.

03:44.340 --> 03:45.430
Oh, my bad!

03:45.510 --> 03:47.140
-Skadi!
-Skadi!

03:47.220 --> 03:48.310
Skadi, please!

03:48.390 --> 03:49.930
While the rent-to-scenery
ratio

03:50.020 --> 03:52.100
is incredible out here
on the fjords,

03:52.190 --> 03:55.560
the winter climate has proven
disastrous to our skin!

03:55.650 --> 03:57.020
It is so dry, Skadi.

03:57.110 --> 03:58.730
We itch, we flake.

03:58.820 --> 03:59.980
We are only mice.

04:00.070 --> 04:01.780
Just a tiny mist would do.

04:01.860 --> 04:03.570
My chapped lips, Skadi.

04:03.660 --> 04:06.660
My friends say I appear
to be 90 years old,

04:06.740 --> 04:08.620
but I am only 4.

04:08.700 --> 04:10.200
And my paws
are so chapped,

04:10.290 --> 04:13.120
they must be wrapped
in bandages always.

04:13.210 --> 04:15.790
My friends call me
"old stinky bandage hands"

04:15.880 --> 04:18.670
to my face, Skadi.
-And my décolletage

04:18.750 --> 04:21.510
is so flaky
I must cover it totally.

04:21.590 --> 04:22.760
A disgrace!

04:22.840 --> 04:24.680
[ Mice shouting indistinctly ]
What?

04:24.760 --> 04:25.640
Uh, wha--

04:25.720 --> 04:27.220
We can't hear you!

04:27.300 --> 04:28.470
Actually they say they --

04:28.550 --> 04:30.600
Come on, Alexa.
You coming?

04:30.680 --> 04:32.600
Yeah, wait up.

04:32.680 --> 04:36.020
Alright, slugger,
your cloud-punching post...

04:36.100 --> 04:37.270
Let me at 'em.

04:37.360 --> 04:38.820
...is at the top
of a little climb

04:38.900 --> 04:40.530
I like
to call "Rude Bird,"

04:40.610 --> 04:43.190
after the rude birds
that like to roost here.

04:43.280 --> 04:46.200
We're gonna climb it
right now.

04:46.280 --> 04:47.660
No problem.

04:47.740 --> 04:49.830
I grab baseball bats
all the time with these fists.

04:49.910 --> 04:52.450
Got calluses for days.
Oh!

04:52.540 --> 04:54.910
I am a callus freak!

04:55.000 --> 04:58.330
Check it out.
My calluses got calluses.

04:58.420 --> 05:00.210
Lemme see yours!
Ha ha.

05:00.290 --> 05:03.590
Skadi, I don't think you could
handle my calluses.

05:03.670 --> 05:07.300
Gnarly.
I like your style.

05:07.390 --> 05:10.430
As far as beta goes, you
basically just follow this crack

05:10.510 --> 05:11.850
till it goes off-width.

05:11.930 --> 05:14.680
Transition this crimpy section
about halfway up.

05:14.770 --> 05:17.150
Lil' dyno up there,
a few super bomber jugs,

05:17.230 --> 05:19.480
and then the crux
is this wild toe hook.

05:19.560 --> 05:20.980
Super-fun.

05:21.070 --> 05:23.860
Last one up has to pick a winner
outta the other's nose!

05:23.940 --> 05:25.950
Climb on!

05:26.030 --> 05:28.450
Unh! Yeah! Unh!

05:28.530 --> 05:29.820
Okay, Alexa.

05:29.910 --> 05:31.990
I know this looks high,
but...you're a giant.

05:32.080 --> 05:34.330
This kinda stuff should be
a breeze for you.

05:34.410 --> 05:36.660
Easy, breezy.

05:36.750 --> 05:39.170
Lemon...squeezy?!

05:39.250 --> 05:41.130
I cannot be stopped!

05:41.210 --> 05:43.340
I am a giant!

05:43.420 --> 05:45.470
Aah! [ Crying ]

05:45.550 --> 05:47.090
Aw, you gonna cry?

05:47.180 --> 05:48.260
What? Never!

05:48.340 --> 05:49.890
There's no crying
in softball.

05:49.970 --> 05:52.060
[ Singsongy voice ]
You're outta your league.

05:52.140 --> 05:53.060
Aah!

05:53.140 --> 05:55.480
Almost there, slugger!

05:55.560 --> 05:57.100
This is my fourth time up.

05:57.190 --> 05:58.520
You're taking it slow, huh?

05:58.600 --> 06:00.400
Really basting in the burn.

06:00.480 --> 06:01.610
I get it.

06:01.690 --> 06:02.730
Yes...I...

06:02.820 --> 06:04.530
live for...the burn.

06:04.610 --> 06:05.780
Ha ha! Heck yeah!

06:05.860 --> 06:07.900
Fist bump!
Yeah...

06:07.990 --> 06:09.240
Must bump...

06:09.320 --> 06:10.740
Fist bump!

06:10.820 --> 06:11.870
[ Farts, sighs ]

06:11.950 --> 06:12.950
There it is!

06:13.030 --> 06:14.620
Unh! Unh! Unh! Unh!

06:14.700 --> 06:15.700
Unh! Unh! Unh!

06:15.790 --> 06:18.580
[ Sighs ]
You got this, Alexa.

06:18.660 --> 06:20.250
You don't got this.

06:20.330 --> 06:22.420
[ Straining ]

06:22.500 --> 06:23.750
[ Shivering ]

06:23.840 --> 06:25.050
There she is!

06:25.130 --> 06:27.550
Yeah,
there's that toe hook!

06:27.630 --> 06:29.470
[ Straining ]

06:29.550 --> 06:32.010
Great, so now that
the easy part's over,

06:32.100 --> 06:34.890
we can move on
to the fun stuff.

06:34.970 --> 06:36.930
Yes...finally...

06:37.020 --> 06:38.100
Fun stuff.

06:38.180 --> 06:39.600
You good, slugger?

06:39.690 --> 06:41.480
[ Sighs ] I'm good!

06:41.560 --> 06:43.770
Ha ha!
That's the spirit!

06:43.860 --> 06:45.860
Now let's hang
from this cliff!

06:45.940 --> 06:47.610
Watch this.

06:49.070 --> 06:50.910
Ahh!

06:50.990 --> 06:53.160
Wait till you feel
the cool breeze

06:53.240 --> 06:56.080
on your soft mossy pits,
Alexa.

06:56.160 --> 06:58.330
Now get out here!

06:58.410 --> 07:00.080
You're a giant.
[ Sighs ]

07:00.160 --> 07:03.630
You're a giant,
you're a giant!

07:03.710 --> 07:06.840
♪♪

07:06.920 --> 07:08.170
Don't look!

07:08.260 --> 07:10.720
It's just a part
of being a giant.

07:10.800 --> 07:12.340
And I won't give up now.

07:12.430 --> 07:14.970
Okay, I'm totally hanging.

07:15.050 --> 07:16.140
What now?

07:16.220 --> 07:17.680
[ Breathes deeply ]

07:17.770 --> 07:21.480
And now we punch clouds to bits
for the benefit of all.

07:21.560 --> 07:23.060
You're a giant,
you're a giant.

07:23.150 --> 07:25.360
These cliff hanging techniques
have been passed down

07:25.440 --> 07:27.780
the giant family
for generations.

07:27.860 --> 07:29.740
[ Grunting ]

07:29.820 --> 07:32.200
Now watch and learn!

07:32.280 --> 07:34.450
-Yay!
-Yay!

07:34.530 --> 07:35.870
Whoo, yeah!

07:35.950 --> 07:39.000
Now let's see
that left hook.

07:39.080 --> 07:41.710
Aah!

07:41.790 --> 07:43.170
Oh, hey.

07:43.250 --> 07:45.540
Looks like there are
no clouds right now.

07:45.630 --> 07:46.630
Darn.

07:46.710 --> 07:48.420
Would you look at that?

07:48.500 --> 07:50.550
It's your lucky day!

07:53.260 --> 07:55.180
Awesome, yes.

07:55.260 --> 07:56.680
So lucky.

07:56.760 --> 07:59.060
[ Straining ]

08:00.770 --> 08:02.100
[ Yawns ] Hm.

08:02.190 --> 08:04.770
I thought I fell asleep
in a sleeping bag?

08:04.850 --> 08:06.980
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my heavens.

08:07.060 --> 08:09.940
Small child, how did you
get into this mess?

08:10.030 --> 08:11.320
Shall I call somebody?

08:11.400 --> 08:13.990
Relay a parting message
to your loved ones?

08:14.070 --> 08:16.700
[ Laughs ] Oh, no.
I'm fine.

08:16.780 --> 08:19.540
This is normal everyday
giant stuff...

08:19.620 --> 08:20.700
right?

08:20.790 --> 08:22.710
Um, what do
giants usually do

08:22.790 --> 08:25.540
when they get
into pickles like this?

08:25.630 --> 08:26.710
Hmm.

08:26.790 --> 08:28.500
Well, my dear, the concept
of pickles

08:28.590 --> 08:31.010
is something
entirely foreign to giants.

08:31.090 --> 08:32.760
I wish you luck.

08:35.640 --> 08:37.390
I don't know
who you're talking to,

08:37.470 --> 08:39.810
but, uh, are you gonna
hit this cloud?

08:39.890 --> 08:41.100
Oh, uh, yeah.

08:41.180 --> 08:42.930
I was just, you know,
hyping myself.

08:43.020 --> 08:44.730
[ Gasps, screams ]
Yikes!

08:44.810 --> 08:45.900
Not in the syllabus.

08:45.980 --> 08:47.060
What do I do?

08:47.150 --> 08:49.270
Softball never prepared me
for this!

08:49.360 --> 08:51.070
I'm just a little kid!

08:53.240 --> 08:55.030
Huh?

08:55.110 --> 08:57.200
Good, I'm alive.

08:57.280 --> 08:58.740
Hey, don't sweat it, rook!

08:58.820 --> 09:01.410
We'll just climb back up
and try again.

09:01.490 --> 09:04.250
[ Groans ]

09:04.330 --> 09:06.540
C'mon, let's go.

09:06.620 --> 09:08.380
Skadi.

09:08.460 --> 09:11.880
I'm about to do something
I've never done before.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.260
No, no, Alexa.

09:13.340 --> 09:16.760
This is the same cliff
we climbed up earlier.

09:16.840 --> 09:18.050
It's not that.

09:18.140 --> 09:19.760
I'm gonna...

09:19.850 --> 09:21.600
give up.

09:21.680 --> 09:25.430
Look, cliff climbing,
cloud punching,

09:25.520 --> 09:28.060
I'm just not made
for this stuff.

09:28.150 --> 09:29.810
Susie was wrong.

09:29.900 --> 09:31.270
I'm not a giant.

09:31.360 --> 09:32.280
It's just...

09:32.360 --> 09:33.530
not my thing.

09:33.610 --> 09:34.990
Here.

09:35.070 --> 09:37.950
I know something that'll be
both our things.

09:40.450 --> 09:42.740
Oof!
Stop licking your lips!

09:42.830 --> 09:44.160
But, Mama, I must!

09:44.250 --> 09:47.000
How else can I assuage
this ceaseless chafing?

09:47.080 --> 09:48.920
Hmm...
You need more salve.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.090
No!
This is but sand!

09:51.170 --> 09:53.590
And you, come over here.
You need salve, as well.

09:53.670 --> 09:57.340
What?!
Papa, it only makes us drier.

09:57.430 --> 10:00.090
But they've always said
exfoliating helps.

10:00.180 --> 10:02.010
A common misconception.

10:02.100 --> 10:05.520
Will our prayers for moisture
ever be answered?

10:06.930 --> 10:10.900
Ahh. Nothing like a good
ol' cup of twilight cocoa.

10:10.980 --> 10:13.820
I hope you can still lift your
mug after all that climbing.

10:13.900 --> 10:14.820
Hey!

10:14.900 --> 10:16.900
Ha ha ha!

10:17.570 --> 10:19.820
Ahh. Oh!

10:19.910 --> 10:21.820
Hot cocoa cloud alert!

10:21.910 --> 10:23.830
-Whee!
-Whee!

10:23.910 --> 10:26.620
-Whee!
-Ahh!

10:26.700 --> 10:28.580
Huh? Could it be?

10:28.660 --> 10:31.250
Mist!
Sweet precipitation!

10:31.330 --> 10:32.920
Le bébé ne pleure plus!

10:34.460 --> 10:36.010
Ahh!

10:36.090 --> 10:39.050
No longer am I
shackled by shame.

10:39.130 --> 10:40.180
-[ Gasps ]
-Whoo-hoo!

10:40.260 --> 10:41.680
I<i> am</i> a giant!

10:41.760 --> 10:43.510
A giant to mice.

10:43.600 --> 10:46.180
Oh!
You<i> are</i> a giant.

10:46.270 --> 10:48.480
You're a giant to mice!

10:48.560 --> 10:49.600
That's what I --

10:49.690 --> 10:51.850
Heh heh. Yeah.

10:51.940 --> 10:53.730
♪♪

10:53.810 --> 10:56.190
-Ooh!
-Ooh!

10:56.280 --> 10:59.240
Alexa:
Feeling good, everyone?

10:59.320 --> 11:02.370
Feeling good, Alexa?

11:02.450 --> 11:04.870
Feelin' good, Skadi?

11:04.950 --> 11:11.670
♪♪

11:11.750 --> 11:18.380
♪♪

11:18.460 --> 11:20.260
You don't got this.
